\c 27
\s1 The Altar
\p
\v 1 “Make an altar\f + \fr 27:1 \fk altar \ft Altar is a high table that often mentioned in PL. This altar is made from stones, that is used as a place to offer animal sacrifices to God. This altar is made from wood so that it can be moved.\f* from acacia wood with a square shape, with the dimensions 2.2 meter in length, 2.2 meter in width, and 1.3 meter in height.\f + \fr 27:1 \fk meter measurements \ft Literally, “five cubits in length and five cubits win width, …. three cubits in height.”\f*
\v 2 Make four horns on the four corners
